8.16.20  9:41 pm   I constantly have trouble creating new stuff and being creative. Most of what I do (music, drawings, etc) are just things that someone else already did. Any tips?

      start by just making a list of things no one has done. this can't be hard, the majority of things have never been done. but it might be easier to think of them when you are not pressured to create it yet. i think once you get 3 or 4 things, it will be impossible to stop, and you'll very quickly have 100 or more things on the list. now your next challenge will be to figure out when to do 100 things

8.16.20  7:55 pm   I couldn't stop thinking about "I might quit" and really just feeling it. I couldnt stop thinking it and wanting to do something with the feelings I felt from it, so I bought a guitar and i've been trying to learn music so I can try to express the things I felt from it. Even though its the wrong question, I wanna know how do I learn how to play to the point that I can express my feelings?

      there are 2 things i can recommend. spending a lot of time with your instrument, preferably by the window, use the instrument to attempt to solve the entire universe. (this is not possible, but it's a good practice exercise). the other thing i would recommend is to learn all the songs you know. (learn them YOURSELF, don't try to have someone else show you, studies show that they are statistically always wrong)
